<br>
First, let me clear up one thing. <br>
<br>
I have no problem losing a duel to anyone. I'll duel anybody, any time. No matter what season they are. If they are blood red, I'll duel em and try to win. If they are green, I'll duel em and try to win. I dont care. A duels a duel and for Zaith, he wont ever stop fighting until he or the other person is dead. <br>
<br>
But over the course of my time here on FV, I have come to realize that a vast majority of people wont duel you unless they can win, and they know it. I have never fought a duel with anyone even conned to me, or yellow to me. They are always Green/DB/ or red. The duels I have fought are, mostly, IC duels. I've beat many red conned people in my day, and lost a few as well. <br>
<br>
While I can understand the mentality of not wanting to lose a fight, I ask people to start thinking like thier character when it comes to duels. Zaith is a Knight. He, thus, has honor, no matter what you Evil/darkies might say. He will fight anyone if they offend his honor, attack his family, guild or friends. Doesnt matter if they are green to him or blood red. He has killed many dark blue conned folks that messed with the younger member of Lust for Blood and he killed lots of red conned members of Lust and others as well. Since he left Lust for Blood, he hasnt dueled as much, but those he has fought have always been red since he left. Some he beat and some he lost. <br>
<br>
Ok. My point, right. Getting to it. <br>
<br>
The other night a group of people came into Neriak and started killing the guards, looking for some conflict RP. I got a /tell from one of my friends who just started an alt and she told me no one was there that was near old enough to fight back. So, Zaith still wishing to defend Neriak, and more so those who cant defend them selves, ran his skinny inky butt over there and stood up to em. They were all red to him at 45. Some had Barons in thier names. My guess is 55+. But he dueled the only person who would fight him, a enchanter. He lost but the enchanter was bragging how he had not lost a fight and has never tasted a blade in a duel. Zaith let him taste his, a few times. <br>
<br>
So they leave. A 55+ SK from Conclave of the Damned, who I've RPed with before, showed up, insulted Zaith and promptly killed him. So Z died twice to people he knew he couldnt beat but it was his duty. <br>
<br>
So whats the fucking deal people? Is everyone SO afraid of losing a duel that you wont fight unless you KNOW you will win? Its a death, thats it. You MIGHT lose some exp but who cares? Its just exp! I lost exp in my duel with the enchanter. <br>
<br>
Conflict, as Shin has so often said, is the core of role play. I agree whole heartedly. With out conflict, you have no real role play, just pansies sitting around singing Kumbeya or what ever.  <br>
<br>
Dont be scared of getting you butt whooped. And just because someone is dark blue or light blue to you doesnt mean you will win. I've proven that point a few times to people.  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/warden4423/newzaith2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
