<br>
a) A group awaits me OR we are killing something and would hurt the raid/group me skipping off midfight to duel<br>
<br>
b) We have dueled 2 or 3 times in a row and green or Red con and it's just becomming silly over fun.<br>
<br>
c) The individual isn't RP'ing and takeing a duel personaly.<br>
<br>
<br>
If they are Dark Blue or lower con and I win, Kaz kills them and takes no pride from the death, it was a nessasary thing that needed to be done.  You draw your blade and kill them.  If I lose Kaz is shamed and would be harsh on himself but show honor to a worthy foe.<br>
<br>
If they are Red con and I win, the death was worthy and honor served, still showing honor to a worthy foe as long as they recieve the victory with proper honor.  Nothing is more sad than a person Red coned to you bragging up the victory as they refuse to duel those above them, I see this happen in about 75% of teh city raids that happen.  I do admit I take quite a bit of pride in the occational victory of the Red con, but again a bragging dance idsn't IC for me.<br>
